{
  "supplemental_canticles": {
    "title": "Supplemental Canticles",
    "slug": "supplemental-canticles",
    "pb_pages": [79, 80, 81, 82, 83, 84, 85, 86, 87, 88],
    "sections": [
      {
        "id": "for_worship",
        "title": "For Worship",
        "pb_page_start": 79,
        "pb_page_end": 88,
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "section_title",
            "size": "3xl",
            "text": "supplemental canticles"
          },
          {
            "type": "section_title",
            "size": "3xl",
            "text": "for worship"
          },
          {
            "type": "section_title",
            "text": "1"
          },
          {
            "type": "section_title",
            "text": "magna et mirabilia"
          },
          {
            "type": "section_title",
            "fancy": true,
            "text": "The Song of the Redeemed"
          },
          {
            "type": "rubric",
            "text": "Especially suitable for use in Advent and Easter"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "text": "O ruler of the universe, Lord God,"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "text": "great deeds are they that you have done, *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "bold": true,
            "text": "surpassing human understanding."
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "text": "Your ways are ways of righteousness and truth, *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "bold": true,
            "text": "O King of all the ages."
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "text": "Who can fail to do you homage, Lord,"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "text": "and sing the praises of your Name? *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "bold": true,
            "text": "For you only are the Holy One."
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "text": "All nations will draw near and fall down before you, *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "bold": true,
            "text": "because your just and holy works have been revealed."
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "bold": true,
            "text": "Glory be to the Father, and to the Son, and to the Holy Spirit; *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "bold": true,
            "text": "as it was in the beginning, is now, and ever shall be,"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "bold": true,
            "ref": "revelation 15:3-4",
            "text": "world without end. Amen."
          },
          {
            "type": "section_title",
            "text": "2"
          },
          {
            "type": "section_title",
            "text": "surge, illuminare"
          },
          {
            "type": "section_title",
            "fancy": true,
            "text": "Arise, shine, for your light has come"
          },
          {
            "type": "rubric",
            "text": "Especially suitable for use during the season after Epiphany"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "text": "Arise, shine, for your light has come, *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "indent": true,
            "text": "and the glory of the Lord has dawned upon you."
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "text": "For behold, darkness covers the land; *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "indent": true,
            "text": "deep gloom enshrouds the peoples."
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "text": "But over you the Lord will rise, *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "indent": true,
            "text": "and his glory will appear upon you."
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "text": "Nations will stream to your light, *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "indent": true,
            "text": "and kings to the brightness of your dawning."
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "text": "Your gates will always be open; *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "indent": true,
            "text": "by day or night they will never be shut."
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "text": "They will call you, The City of the Lord, *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "indent": true,
            "text": "the Zion of the Holy One of Israel."
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "text": "Violence will no more be heard in your land, *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "indent": true,
            "text": "ruin or destruction within your borders."
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "text": "You will call your walls, Salvation, *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "indent": true,
            "text": "and all your portals, Praise."
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "text": "The sun will no more be your light by day; *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "indent": true,
            "text": "by night you will not need the brightness of the moon."
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "text": "The Lord will be your everlasting light, *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "indent": true,
            "text": "and your God will be your glory."
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "text": "Glory be to the Father, and to the Son, and to the Holy Spirit; *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "indent": true,
            "text": "as it was in the beginning, is now, and ever shall be,"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "indent": true,
            "ref": "isaiah 60:1-3, 11, 14, 18-19",
            "text": "world without end. Amen."
          },
          {
            "type": "section_title",
            "text": "3"
          },
          {
            "type": "section_title",
            "text": "kyrie Pantokrator"
          },
          {
            "type": "section_title",
            "fancy": true,
            "text": "A Song of Penitence"
          },
          {
            "type": "rubric",
            "text": "Especially suitable for use during Lent"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "text": "O Lord and Ruler of the hosts of heaven, *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "bold": true,
            "text": "God of Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob,"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "bold": true,
            "text": "and of all their righteous offspring:"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "text": "You made the heavens and the earth, *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "bold": true,
            "text": "with all their vast array."
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "text": "All things quake with fear at your presence; *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "bold": true,
            "text": "they tremble because of your power."
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "text": "But your merciful promise is beyond all measure; *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "bold": true,
            "text": "it surpasses all that our minds can fathom."
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "text": "O Lord, you are full of compassion, *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "bold": true,
            "text": "long-suffering, and abounding in mercy."
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "text": "You hold back your hand; *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "bold": true,
            "text": "you do not punish as we deserve."
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "text": "In your great goodness, Lord,"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "text": "you have promised forgiveness to sinners, *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "bold": true,
            "text": "that they may repent of their sin and be saved."
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "text": "And now, O Lord, I bend the knee of my heart, *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "bold": true,
            "text": "and make my appeal, sure of your gracious goodness."
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "text": "I have sinned, O Lord, I have sinned, *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "bold": true,
            "text": "and I know my wickedness only too well."
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "text": "Therefore I make this prayer to you: *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "bold": true,
            "text": "Forgive me, Lord, forgive me."
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "text": "Do not let me perish in my sin, *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "bold": true,
            "text": "nor condemn me to the depths of the earth."
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "text": "For you, O Lord, are the God of those who repent, *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "bold": true,
            "text": "and in me you will show forth your goodness."
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "text": "Unworthy as I am, you will save me,"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "text": "in accordance with your great mercy, *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "bold": true,
            "text": "and I will praise you without ceasing all the days of my life."
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "text": "For all the powers of heaven sing your praises, *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "bold": true,
            "ref": "prayer of manasseh, 1-2, 4, 6-7, 11-15",
            "text": "and yours is the glory to ages of ages. Amen."
          },
          {
            "type": "section_title",
            "text": "4"
          },
          {
            "type": "section_title",
            "text": "quaerite dominum"
          },
          {
            "type": "section_title",
            "fancy": true,
            "text": "Seek the Lord while he wills to be found"
          },
          {
            "type": "rubric",
            "text": "Especially suitable for use during Lent"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "text": "Seek the Lord while he wills to be found; *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "bold": true,
            "text": "call upon him when he draws near."
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "text": "Let the wicked forsake their ways *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "bold": true,
            "text": "and the evil ones their thoughts;"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "text": "And let them turn to the Lord, and he will have compassion, *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "bold": true,
            "text": "and to our God, for he will richly pardon."
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "text": "For my thoughts are not your thoughts, *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "bold": true,
            "text": "nor your ways my ways, says the Lord."
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "text": "For as the heavens are higher than the earth, *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "bold": true,
            "text": "so are my ways higher than your ways,"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "bold": true,
            "text": "and my thoughts than your thoughts."
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "text": "For as rain and snow fall from the heavens *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "bold": true,
            "text": "and return not again, but water the earth,"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "text": "Bringing forth life and giving growth, *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "bold": true,
            "text": "seed for sowing and bread for eating,"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "text": "So is my word that goes forth from my mouth; *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "bold": true,
            "text": "it will not return to me empty;"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "text": "But it will accomplish that which I have purposed, *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "bold": true,
            "text": "and prosper in that for which I sent it."
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "text": "Glory be to the Father, and to the Son, and to the Holy Spirit; *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "bold": true,
            "text": "as it was in the beginning, is now, and ever shall be,"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "bold": true,
            "ref": "isaiah 55:6-11",
            "text": "world without end. Amen."
          },
          {
            "type": "section_title",
            "text": "5"
          },
          {
            "type": "section_title",
            "text": "cantemus domino"
          },
          {
            "type": "section_title",
            "fancy": true,
            "text": "The Song of Moses"
          },
          {
            "type": "rubric",
            "text": "Especially suitable for use in Easter"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "text": "I will sing to the Lord, for he is lofty and uplifted; *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "bold": true,
            "text": "the horse and its rider has he hurled into the sea."
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "text": "The Lord is my strength and my refuge; *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "bold": true,
            "text": "the Lord has become my Savior."
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "text": "This is my God and I will praise him, *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "bold": true,
            "text": "the God of my people and I will exalt him."
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "text": "The Lord is a mighty warrior; *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "bold": true,
            "text": "The Lord is his Name."
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "text": "The chariots of Pharaoh and his army has he hurled into the sea; *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "bold": true,
            "text": "the finest of those who bear armor"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "bold": true,
            "text": "have been drowned in the Red Sea."
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "text": "The fathomless deep has overwhelmed them; *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "bold": true,
            "text": "they sank into the depths like a stone."
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "text": "Your right hand, O Lord, is glorious in might; *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "bold": true,
            "text": "your right hand, O Lord, has overthrown the enemy."
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "text": "Who can be compared with you, O Lord, among the gods? *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "bold": true,
            "text": "Who is like you, glorious in holiness,"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "bold": true,
            "text": "awesome in renown, and worker of wonders?"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "text": "You stretched forth your right hand; *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "bold": true,
            "text": "the earth swallowed them up."
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "text": "With your constant love you led the people you redeemed; *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "bold": true,
            "text": "you brought them in safety to your holy dwelling."
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "text": "You will bring them in and plant them *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "bold": true,
            "text": "on the mount of your possession,"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "text": "The resting-place you have made for yourself, O Lord, *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "bold": true,
            "text": "the sanctuary, O Lord, that your hand has established."
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "text": "The Lord shall reign *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "bold": true,
            "text": "for ever and for ever."
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "text": "Glory be to the Father, and to the Son, and to the Holy Spirit; *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "bold": true,
            "text": "as it was in the beginning, is now, and ever shall be,"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "bold": true,
            "ref": "exodus 15:1-6, 11-13, 17-18",
            "text": "world without end. Amen."
          },
          {
            "type": "section_title",
            "text": "6"
          },
          {
            "type": "section_title",
            "text": "dignu es"
          },
          {
            "type": "section_title",
            "fancy": true,
            "text": "A Song to the Lamb"
          },
          {
            "type": "rubric",
            "text": "Especially suitable for use after Ascension and in Easter Season"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "text": "Splendor and honor and kingly power *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "bold": true,
            "text": "are yours by right, O Lord our God,"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "text": "For you created everything that is, *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "bold": true,
            "text": "and by your will they were created and have their being;"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "text": "And yours by right, O Lamb that was slain, *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "bold": true,
            "text": "for with your blood you have redeemed for God,"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "text": "From every family, language, people, and nation, *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "bold": true,
            "text": "a kingdom of priests to serve our God."
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "text": "And so, to him who sits upon the throne, *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "bold": true,
            "text": "and to Christ the Lamb,"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "text": "Be worship and praise, dominion and splendor, *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "bold": true,
            "ref": "revelation 4:11; 5:9-10, 13, 14",
            "text": "for ever and for evermore. Amen."
          },
          {
            "type": "section_title",
            "text": "7"
          },
          {
            "type": "section_title",
            "text": "cantate domino"
          },
          {
            "type": "section_title",
            "fancy": true,
            "text": "Sing unto the Lord"
          },
          {
            "type": "rubric",
            "text": "Especially suitable for use in Easter and at any time outside penitential seasons"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "text": "O sing unto the Lord a new song, *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "bold": true,
            "text": "for he has done marvelous things."
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "text": "With his own right hand, and with his holy arm, *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "bold": true,
            "text": "he has won for himself the victory."
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "text": "The Lord declared his salvation; *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "bold": true,
            "text": "his righteousness he has openly shown in the sight of the nations."
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "text": "He has remembered his mercy and truth toward the house of Israel,*"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "bold": true,
            "text": "and all the ends of the world have seen the salvation of our God."
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "text": "Show yourselves joyful unto the Lord, all you lands; *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "bold": true,
            "text": "sing, rejoice, and give thanks."
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "text": "Praise the Lord with the harp; *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "bold": true,
            "text": "sing with the harp a psalm of thanksgiving."
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "text": "With trumpets also and horns, *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "bold": true,
            "text": "O show yourselves joyful before the Lord, the King."
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "text": "Let the sea make a noise, and all that is in it, *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "bold": true,
            "text": "the round world, and those that dwell therein."
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "text": "Let the rivers clap their hands, and let the hills be joyful"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "text": "together before the Lord, *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "bold": true,
            "text": "for he has come to judge the earth."
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "text": "With righteousness shall he judge the world *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "bold": true,
            "text": "and the peoples with equity."
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "text": "Glory be to the Father, and to the Son, and to the Holy Spirit; *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "bold": true,
            "text": "as it was in the beginning, is now, and ever shall be,"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "bold": true,
            "ref": "psalm 98",
            "text": "world without end. Amen."
          },
          {
            "type": "section_title",
            "text": "8"
          },
          {
            "type": "section_title",
            "text": "ecce, deus"
          },
          {
            "type": "section_title",
            "fancy": true,
            "text": "Surely, it is God who saves me"
          },
          {
            "type": "rubric",
            "text": "Suitable for use at any time"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "text": "Surely, it is God who saves me; *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "bold": true,
            "text": "I will trust in him and not be afraid."
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "text": "For the Lord is my stronghold and my sure defense, *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "bold": true,
            "text": "and he will be my Savior."
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "text": "Therefore you shall draw water with rejoicing *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "bold": true,
            "text": "from the springs of salvation."
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "text": "And on that day you shall say, *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "bold": true,
            "text": "Give thanks to the Lord and call upon his Name;"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "text": "Make his deeds known among the peoples; *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "bold": true,
            "text": "see that they remember that his Name is exalted."
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "text": "Sing the praises of the Lord, for he has done great things, *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "bold": true,
            "text": "and this is known in all the world."
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "text": "Cry aloud, inhabitants of Zion, ring out your joy, *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "bold": true,
            "text": "for the great one in the midst of you is the Holy One of Israel."
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "text": "Glory be to the Father, and to the Son, and to the Holy Spirit; *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "bold": true,
            "text": "as it was in the beginning, is now, and ever shall be,"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "bold": true,
            "ref": "isaiah 12:2-6",
            "text": "world without end. Amen."
          },
          {
            "type": "section_title",
            "text": "9"
          },
          {
            "type": "section_title",
            "text": "deus misereatur"
          },
          {
            "type": "section_title",
            "fancy": true,
            "text": "God be merciful"
          },
          {
            "type": "rubric",
            "text": "Suitable for use at any time"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "text": "May God be merciful unto us, and bless us, *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "bold": true,
            "text": "and show us the light of his countenance, and be merciful"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "bold": true,
            "text": "unto us."
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "text": "Let your way be known upon earth, *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "bold": true,
            "text": "your saving health among all nations."
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "text": "Let the peoples praise you, O God; *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "bold": true,
            "text": "indeed, let all the peoples praise you."
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "text": "O let the nations rejoice and be glad, *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "bold": true,
            "text": "for you shall judge the peoples righteously, and govern"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "bold": true,
            "text": "the nations upon earth."
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "text": "Let the peoples praise you, O God; *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "bold": true,
            "text": "let all the peoples praise you."
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "text": "Then shall the earth bring forth her increase, *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "bold": true,
            "text": "and God, even our own God, shall give us his blessing."
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "bold": true,
            "text": "God shall bless us, *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "bold": true,
            "ref": "psalm 67",
            "text": "and all the ends of the world shall fear him."
          },
          {
            "type": "section_title",
            "text": "10"
          },
          {
            "type": "section_title",
            "text": "benedicite, onmia opera domini"
          },
          {
            "type": "section_title",
            "fancy": true,
            "text": "A Song of Creation"
          },
          {
            "type": "rubric",
            "text": "Especially suitable for use on Saturday"
          },
          {
            "type": "section_title",
            "latin_size": true,
            "text": "invocation"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "text": "Glorify the Lord, all you works of the Lord, *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "text": "praise him and highly exalt him for ever."
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "text": "In the firmament of his power, glorify the Lord, *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "text": "praise him and highly exalt him for ever."
          },
          {
            "type": "section_title",
            "latin_size": true,
            "text": "i. the cosmic order"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "text": "Glorify the Lord, you angels and all powers of the Lord, *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "text": "O heavens and all waters above the heavens."
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "text": "Sun and moon and stars of the sky, glorify the Lord, *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "text": "praise him and highly exalt him for ever."
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "text": "Glorify the Lord, every shower of rain and fall of dew, *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "text": "all winds and fire and heat."
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "text": "Winter and summer, glorify the Lord, *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "text": "praise him and highly exalt him for ever."
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "text": "Glorify the Lord, O chill and cold, *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "text": "drops of dew and flakes of snow."
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "text": "Frost and cold, ice and sleet, glorify the Lord, *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "text": "praise him and highly exalt him for ever."
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "text": "Glorify the Lord, O nights and days, *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "text": "O shining light and enfolding dark."
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "text": "Storm clouds and thunderbolts, glorify the Lord, *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "text": "praise him and highly exalt him for ever."
          },
          {
            "type": "section_title",
            "latin_size": true,
            "text": "ii. the earth and its creatures"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "text": "Let the earth glorify the Lord, *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "text": "praise him and highly exalt him for ever."
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "text": "Glorify the Lord, O mountains and hills,"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "text": "and all that grows upon the earth, *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "text": "praise him and highly exalt him for ever."
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "text": "Glorify the Lord, O springs of water, seas, and streams, *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "text": "O whales and all that move in the waters."
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "text": "All birds of the air, glorify the Lord, *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "text": "praise him and highly exalt him for ever."
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "text": "Glorify the Lord, O beasts of the wild, *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "text": "and all you flocks and herds."
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "text": "O men and women everywhere, glorify the Lord, *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "text": "praise him and highly exalt him for ever."
          },
          {
            "type": "section_title",
            "latin_size": true,
            "text": "iii. the people of god"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "text": "Let the people of God glorify the Lord, *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "text": "praise him and highly exalt him for ever."
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "text": "Glorify the Lord, O priests and servants of the Lord, *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "text": "praise him and highly exalt him for ever."
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "text": "Glorify the Lord, O spirits and souls of the righteous, *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "text": "praise him and highly exalt him for ever."
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "text": "You that are holy and humble of heart, glorify the Lord, *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "text": "praise him and highly exalt him for ever."
          },
          {
            "type": "section_title",
            "latin_size": true,
            "text": "doxology"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "text": "Let us glorify the Lord: the Father, the Son, and the Holy Spirit; *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "text": "praise him and highly exalt him for ever."
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "text": "In the firmament of his power, glorify the Lord, *"
          },
          {
            "type": "line",
            "indent": true,
            "ref": "song of the three young men, 35-65",
            "text": "praise him and highly exalt him for ever."
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
}
